  "statement": {
    "en": "Borwein integral: ∫₀^∞ sinc(x)·sinc(x/3)·sinc(x/5)·…·sinc(x/(2k+1)) dx equals exactly π/2 for k=0,1,…,7, but fails at k=8 when the sum 1/3+1/5+…+1/15 first exceeds 1. The 'breaking point' is the point where overlapping supports in Fourier space first cover the origin.",
    "ja": null,
    "latex": "\\int_0^\\infty \\prod_{k=0}^{N} \\mathrm{sinc}(x/(2k+1)) dx",
